Business Brief -- New Plan Realty Trust:
   Company Contracts to Buy
   Properties for $53.2 Million
He said the company's strong cash position will enable it
to exploit the pressures many developers feel these days from
their lenders. "The market is terrible if you are a seller,"
he said. "If you are a buyer, it's a wonderful market." He
said the company plans to make more acquisitions in the
future.
   The portfolio contains two properties in Alabama, two in
Tennessee, one in Florida and one in Indiana.
   Excluding the new properties, New Plan, which is based in
New York, has interests in 66 shopping centers and 10 garden
apartment complexes.